div.p:
But, while his Naval ſtrength is unbroken;
while he has that Chain of
Fortified Towns upon the Rhine;
and that formidable Barrier in Flanders;
while on the ſide of Spain, Italy,
and Switzerland, he is left in ſuch
a condition to Invade, and ſo fortified
againſt Invaſion, we may make
a Peace that ſhall give us preſent eaſe,
and put off the Evil day for a time,


but we cannot pretend to have ſecur'd
our Liberties, or defeated his
deſigns of Univerſal Monarchy.
